  <mads:note type="source">"Ariston, 6, epigrammatic poet, author of three epigrams from the
      'Garland' of Meleager, but not of Anth. Pal. 9,77, ascribed by Planudes to either A. or
      Hermodorus, but by codex P to Antipater of Thessalonica, which seems more plausible....."
      Degani, Enzo (Bologna). "Ariston." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert
      Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2007. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 19 July
      2007</mads:note>  
